		<!-- The body of the document contains a number of sections -->
		<section name="Installing HAPI TestPanel">

			<subsection name="Setting up Eclipse">

				<p>
					Building TestPanel should be possible under any environment, but
					using Eclipse is recommended. First set up your	environment:
				</p>

				<ul>
					<li>
						Install 
						<a href="http://maven.apache.org">Maven</a> 
						(3.0 or newer) and ensure it works from the command	line.
					</li>
					<li>
						Install the
						<a href="http://www.eclipse.org/windowbuilder/download.php">Windowbuilder</a>
						plugin into Eclipse.
					</li>
				</ul>

			</subsection>
			<subsection name="Check out the Project">
	
				<p>
					Next, check out the HAPI
					<a href="https://hl7api.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/hl7api/trunk/hapi-mvn/">root project</a>.
				</p>
				
			</subsection>

		</section>

	</body>

